    • Constructor Detail

      • Collection

        public Collection(String prefix,
                  String displayId,
                  String version)
           throws SBOLValidationException
        Creates a Collection instance with the given arguments.

        If the given prefix does not end with one of the following delimiters: "/", ":", or "#", then "/" is appended to the end of it.

        This method requires the given prefix, displayId, and version are not null and valid.

        A Collection instance is created with a compliant URI. This URI is composed from the given prefix, the given displayId, and version. The display ID, persistent identity, and version fields of this instance are then set accordingly.

        Parameters:
        prefix -
        displayId -
        version -
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the defaultURIprefix is null
        SBOLValidationException - if the given URIprefix is null
        SBOLValidationException - if the given URIprefix is non-compliant
        SBOLValidationException - if the given displayId is invalid
        SBOLValidationException - if the given version is invalid

      • removeMember

        public boolean removeMember(URI memberURI)
                     throws SBOLValidationException
        Removes the given member reference from the set of member references.

        If this Collection object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        memberURI - the reference to a TopLevel object to be removed from the SBOL Document.
        Returns:
        true if the matching member reference is removed successfully, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException

      • setMembers

        public void setMembers(Set<URI> members)
                throws SBOLValidationException
        Clears the existing set of member references first, then adds the given set of the member references to this Collection object.

        If this Collection object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Parameters:
        members - A set of URI references to zero or more TopLevel objects within the SBOL Document.
        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException

      • clearMembers

        public void clearMembers()
                  throws SBOLValidationException
        Removes all entries of this Collection object's set of reference member URIs. The set will be empty after this call returns.

        If this Collection object belongs to an SBOLDocument instance, then the SBOLDcouement instance is checked for compliance first. Only a compliant SBOLDocument instance is allowed to be edited.

        Throws:
        SBOLValidationException - if the associated SBOLDocument is not compliant
